The paper focuses on recommendation systems, which are commonly studied in the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of various machine learning algorithms and neural networks also suggests a potential fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The evaluation of the system in the context of video-streaming suggests a potential fit for the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of a field study and post-analysis suggests a potential fit for the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
